Class LShape

  • java.lang.Object
    • hw4.AbstractShape
      • hw4.LShape
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    api.Shape, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class LShape
extends AbstractShape
    Implementation of LShape. An LShape is an abstract shape that has initial cell ordering at (0, 0): {(0, 0), (1, -2), (1, -1), (1, 0)}. The transform will be ccw (the normal, inherited transform). The color of this shape will be ORANGE.
    Author:
    SMSheets@IAState.edu - Steven Marshall Sheets
